** Assembly with Two Parts and Contact Definition
** Sample 2: Multi-part assembly with contact interaction
*PART, NAME=PART_MASTER
*NODE
 1, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0
 2, 1.0, 0.0, 0.0
 3, 1.0, 1.0, 0.0
 4, 0.0, 1.0, 0.0
*ELEMENT, TYPE=S4, ELSET=MASTER_SURF
 1, 1, 2, 3, 4
*SURFACE, NAME=MASTER_CONTACT
 MASTER_SURF, SPOS
*END PART
*PART, NAME=PART_SLAVE
*NODE
 11, 0.0, 0.0, 0.1
 12, 1.0, 0.0, 0.1
 13, 1.0, 1.0, 0.1
 14, 0.0, 1.0, 0.1
*ELEMENT, TYPE=S4, ELSET=SLAVE_SURF
 11, 11, 12, 13, 14
*SURFACE, NAME=SLAVE_CONTACT
 SLAVE_SURF, SNEG
*END PART
*ASSEMBLY, NAME=ASSEMBLY_1
*INSTANCE, PART=PART_MASTER, NAME=MASTER_INSTANCE
*END INSTANCE
*INSTANCE, PART=PART_SLAVE, NAME=SLAVE_INSTANCE
*END INSTANCE
*CONTACT PAIR, INTERACTION=CONTACT_1, TYPE=SURFACE TO SURFACE
 MASTER_INSTANCE.MASTER_CONTACT, SLAVE_INSTANCE.SLAVE_CONTACT
*END ASSEMBLY
*INTERACTION, NAME=CONTACT_1
*SURFACE INTERACTION
*FRICTION, SLIP RATE DEPENDENT
 0.5, 0.3
*END ASSEMBLY
